Israeli sociologists see the two trends as closely related to each other. Their studies find that liberal pro-choice laws are likely to cause a sharp increase in the number of illegal abortions for every additional restriction passed.

Despite being in direct violation of the right to life of the unborn, legalizing abortion endorses uninsured mothers “harassing” the system with a range of health complaints that are “caused by their own bad conduct.” This is cattle welfare code language to preempt any debate over the worthiness of examining and discussing the man-made causes behind a women’s many health ailments that can include vague symptoms; soaring rates of gastrointestinal disorders, skin diseases, depression, anxiety, and a wealth of autoimmune diseases, with a higher medication side effect profile compared to the U.S.

According to the latest statistics published in The Algemeiner, and detailed in a separate reader report to this blog, legal abortion in Israel save women from genetically defective unborn children and fetuses whose brain damage may continue into adulthood. It is presumed that the short informational campaign in Egyptian airports is based on a similar rationale. This is an apropos time to think about the human rights, living conditions and quality of life of all women.
